00:32:34,401 --> 00:32:34,882
Challenges of editing.

787
00:32:40,073 --> 00:32:42,214
We had some limitations with Maya

788
00:32:42,214 --> 00:32:44,295
because blending takes together is hard.

789
00:32:44,295 --> 00:32:46,336
We weren't having too much luck with the tracks editor,

790
00:32:46,336 --> 00:32:47,816
so what we ended up doing was using

791
00:32:47,816 --> 00:32:49,517
Motion Builder's Story tool,

792
00:32:49,517 --> 00:32:51,337
which let us edit pretty quickly

793
00:32:51,337 --> 00:32:53,278
and get some macro edits going.

794
00:32:53,278 --> 00:32:55,139
And then once we were happy with the rough timing,

795
00:32:55,139 --> 00:32:58,100
we could then work on anim layers and constraints.

796
00:32:58,100 --> 00:33:01,381
Now there's a bit of an art to choosing where to edit.

797
00:33:01,381 --> 00:33:02,861
You're trying to find the best blend.

798
00:33:02,861 --> 00:33:05,823
And what you're looking for is character position and pose,

799
00:33:05,823 --> 00:33:07,143
whether they match pretty closely

800
00:33:07,143 --> 00:33:08,383
across two different takes.

801
00:33:09,192 --> 00:33:10,734
Of course, also the camera position.

802
00:33:10,734 --> 00:33:11,975
Again, because we're not cutting,

803
00:33:11,975 --> 00:33:14,457
you need to make sure the camera's in a pretty safe place

804
00:33:14,457 --> 00:33:16,038
so that you're not getting some weird motion

805
00:33:16,038 --> 00:33:17,900
once you're going between the two takes.

806
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:19,821
It's a bonus if your carriages are off-screen

807
00:33:19,821 --> 00:33:21,363
when you're doing the edit,

808
00:33:21,363 --> 00:33:23,444
because then you don't have to worry

809
00:33:23,444 --> 00:33:25,306
about blending them together.

