00:35:15,669 --> 00:35:18,310
to help us get our workflow moving more quickly.

852
00:35:18,310 --> 00:35:18,710
Oh yes, animation.

853
00:35:18,710 --> 00:35:19,370
It's time to do the fun stuff.

854
00:35:19,370 --> 00:35:24,153
It's time to animate those cool creatures

855
00:35:24,153 --> 00:35:26,374
and those crazy stunts.

856
00:35:27,305 --> 00:35:31,406
And also the not so fun stuff like bandages and chains

857
00:35:31,406 --> 00:35:35,108
and ropes and vines and all those spline IK

858
00:35:35,108 --> 00:35:35,948
everybody loves to do, yeah.

859
00:35:35,948 --> 00:35:39,910
When you're using cuts, it's often simpler

860
00:35:39,910 --> 00:35:43,371
to compartmentalize your thoughts into smaller task chunks

861
00:35:43,371 --> 00:35:45,152
and focus on one shot at a time,

862
00:35:45,152 --> 00:35:46,412
such as this 150 frames, that's not too bad,

863
00:35:46,412 --> 00:35:48,613
you can keep track of what your curves are doing there.

864
00:35:49,724 --> 00:35:51,745
But with very long runners like God of War had,

865
00:35:51,745 --> 00:35:54,266
the animators had to keep the entire scene in mind

866
00:35:54,266 --> 00:35:55,126
while they're making edits,

867
00:35:55,126 --> 00:35:56,747
because if you're working on a layer

868
00:35:56,747 --> 00:35:58,367
and you make a change and you forget

869
00:35:58,367 --> 00:35:59,468
that you made that change,

870
00:35:59,468 --> 00:36:01,088
it might ripple down the entire scene.

871
00:36:01,088 --> 00:36:02,349
So if you're not keeping track,

872
00:36:02,349 --> 00:36:04,850
hours of your work could get wrecked.

873
00:36:04,850 --> 00:36:06,230
The actual process of animating

874
00:36:06,230 --> 00:36:07,911
is the same as it's been for years,

875
00:36:07,911 --> 00:36:10,892
but the mental focus required grew quite a bit.

876
00:36:10,892 --> 00:36:12,753
So let's take a look at some of our awesome

877
00:36:12,753 --> 00:36:15,334
and keyed animations.

